<br>
problems:<br>
<br>
* having a 550dd proc might be a bit nuts<br>
* 2 minutes is a short duration, you'd have to refresh even through a vindicator fight<br>
<br>
maybe a complete rewamp is needed :/ almost all poisons are useless anyway, so i wouldn't mind having them downgraded if you could proc them....would be really sweet.<br>
<br>
some proc suggestions:<br>
<br>
* 50, 100, 200dd<br>
* 20, 30, 50% slow, 2 minute duration<br>
* 50% snare, 1-3 minute duration (scaled with lvl)<br>
* 100/200/300 undead, animal, summoned dd<br>
* 200/400/600 dot over 2 minutes<br>
* 0.5, 1, 2 second stun proc<br>
* stat debuff, something like negative 10, 20, 35 to str/agi/dex<br>
<br>
i'd suggest a 30 minute duration, or - if - they make poisons stackable, maybe 15 minutes.<br>
<br>
components could remain largely the same, perhaps with some changed. the really good poisons would require the hard stuff from TT/EJ, while lower versions could use drops from newbie mobs. <p><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21797">Marauder Prodigious Prodigy</a><br>
Fennin Ro</font><br>
<img src="http://prod.homepage.dk/pics/1106bs.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uravenwingedangel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenwinged Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 10:32:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> I think they would have to be reapplied in the middle of a fight like Vindicator(well, not Vindi, it doesn't take 2 minutes to kill Vindi on my server, maybe some of the other high hp mobs).  15 minutes of proccing on one poison?  As a rogue with a high dex, I can get alot of proc off in 2 minutes.<br>
<br>
Thats just my opinion though, 2 minutes would be balanced with the effects they have currently.<br>
<br>
I mean, if you had 15 minute poison procs, there would be no reason to make them stackable or charged. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujulesbrown.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jules Brown</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 10:02:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2346.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish they would fix poison by...</span><hr size=1> No, procs suck and can't be counted on.  The greatest use of our poisons, such as the slow or resist debuffs, is an EARLY application of the effect.<br>
<br>
Changing poisons to random procs would totally ruin even that last aspect of usefulness for poisons.  You want procs, get a weapon with the proc you like.<br>
<br>
Poisons should be improved by:<br>
1.  Getting rid of the farmed components (more like alchemy)<br>
2.  Some way to get charges on poisons (stacks of 20, whatever)<br>
3.  Adding more USEFUL, STACKABLE, effects.<br>
4.  Allowing for poison re-application without sitting (maybe as an AA) <p><a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3194">Jules, 60 pal</a>  [<a href="http://pub22.ezboard.com/bdaevents">Dark Advocates</a>] 
